1)The average bandwith of wifi is 40 MHz
2)Wifi has Channels 1, 6, and 11 are the most frequently used for 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi.
3)They use the channels 1, 6, and 11, so that peoples internet isn't slow
4)WEP WPA and WPA-2 are security sytems that are built in with the wifi with your permission
5)WPA-2 is most secure because it has a better security system with a personel password
6) AirSnort is a wireless LAN (WLAN) tool which cracks encryption keys on 802.11b WEP networks. AirSnort operates by passively monitoring transmissions, computing the encryption key when enough packets have been gathered
7) Kismet is a network detector, packet sniffer, and intrusion detection system for 802.11 wireless LANs. Kismet will work with any wireless card which supports raw monitoring mode, and can sniff 802.11a, 802.11b, 802.11g, and 802.11n traffic
8) Its a wifi hotspot
